oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Powerhouse at Cherokee Dam
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: General view of the powerhouse at Cherokee Dam looking southeast from the right bank about 200 feet downstream from the axis of dam.
Cherokee Dam is a hydroelectric dam that was built by the Tennessee Valley Authority in the early 1940's as a result of the need for energy during the beginning of World War II.
